<br>
Ahazi server, June 22 2003. 11:45 pm pst. The first ever player deed rebel outpost was placed and had completed it's 5 hour build time 300m east of the npc static base between Anchorhead and Bestine. <br>
A rype hotbed of PVP if there ever was one, and the most logical location for our base.<br>
<br>
It started out with a group of about 8 rebels with pets busy flattening terrian to make room for the base. When we finally placed it word got to the imperials in Bestine somehow and several raiding groups tried to beat us down. We were able to successfully push back 2 major offensives and several skirmishes. One of the major battles earlier on was the most impressive display i'd seen yet [this would soon be overshadowed by the completion of the base...]!<br>
<br>
We finally got the base built, after killing time in Bestine and getting rolled we limped back and redeclaired to find that teh base was at 5 minutes remaining. We stood watch till it was done. then *POOF* appears the rebe base. First impressions was it was pretty small for being so expensive a deed. But oh well. I ran inside [being the first to enter the base woot!] and noticed a mission terminal. The terminal is NOT faction however, everyone was rather upset about that and we /bugged it. I immediately donated a rebel faction scanner to the base--which autoplaces deeds in defense locations [IE, if you want to defend the base, just donate the deed to the HQ terminal, dont try placing the deeds yourself]. Someone else donated a turret, which immediately started shooting the side of the base wall [good work devs =)].<br>
<br>
We noticed the abundance of guards--several of which were commando and general rank! So I took it on myself to &quot;advertise&quot; our new home to the imperials in Bestine. I took my 2nd account bot character and whipped up a sufficiently annoying spam message, assigning it to my f8 key and setting out for the short jog from anchorhead to bestine I snickered to myself at how this would get the imperials riled up good.<br>
<br>
The message went something like this...<br>
<br>
<br>
quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
FREE BANTHA BISCUIT!!!!! To all the REBEL DOGS who want to test their skill DYING against our new Rebel Faction Base.<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Sure enough the message was recieved by several imperial members. Soon after we had what we asked for. The first real test of the bases defenses. It lasted about 4 minutes, but after all was said and done the Imperials were rolled easily.<br>
<br>
Limping back home and licking their wounds, they begain working on getting sufficient faction points to purchase an ATST. They finally got one the next day [June 23 2003] and I was informed they were coming from my imperial insider. They decided to come at us from the South East--the same direction the static npc rebel base was, which took us by surprise quite a bit! Good strategy guys!<br>
<br>
This was my first look at the ATST in action. Doing easily over 1000 heath dmg per hit it was a MACHINE OF DOOM! Unfortunately for the imperials, we can call our pets from the base, but the imperials have limited area to call a camp to do the same.<br>
<br>
This battle lasted MUCH longer, easily over 20 minutes. IN the end only the ATST was left. Our entire rebel army pounded it down into the ground, but at around 60% health the owner recalled it and our fun was ruined. Over all it was a VERY impressive fight!<br>
<br>
This area is goign to be a HOTBED of pvp after launch, I am looking forward to it a lot!<br>
<br>
After the battle we had a massive fireworks display to celebrate our glorious victory over the imperials!!!<br>
<br>
